    "body": "Users who wish to have line numbers enabled in the terminal can use an autocommand:\r\n\r\n```vim\r\nau TermOpen * setlocal number relativenumber\r\n```",
    "closed_at": "2024-12-04T14:40:01Z",
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "No objection. IIRC the reason for inheriting this current window options, was to avoid jank when switching to/from a `:terminal` in the current window. Also, it's just a \"lighter touch\" to let the user's options decide, instead of deciding for them. According to https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/6796 , 'relativenumber' should already be disabled, I guess that changed at some point.\r\n\r\nThis would be less urgent if we move forward with https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/24914 ?",
