            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": ">IIRC the reason for inheriting this current window options, was to avoid jank when switching to/from a :terminal in the current window.\r\n\r\nDo you recall what the issue was? I think with the multi-indexed options (`vim.wo[0][0]`) this works smoothly: the options are only set for the terminal buffer in the window.\r\n\r\nTrying this:\r\n\r\n```\r\nVIMRUNTIME=runtime build/bin/nvim --clean --cmd 'set number' README.md\r\n```\r\n\r\nThen open a new window and create a terminal: `:vsplit|term`. The terminal buffer has no line numbers. Now switch back to the alt buffer `:e #` and the line numbers are back.",
